# Project-Specific Rules
# These are tailored to this Astro project

   <astro>
   When working with Astro:
   - Leverage Astro islands for interactive components
   - Use .astro files for pages with minimal JavaScript
   - Follow Astro's component structure
   - Implement partial hydration when possible
   - Use Astro.glob() for content collection
   - Consider serverless capabilities
   </astro>

<components>
   For components:
   - Keep components modular and reusable
   - Follow atomic design principles (atoms, molecules, organisms)
   - Use props for configuration
   - Document prop types and default values
   - Implement proper state management
   - Use CSS modules or CSS-in-JS for styling
   - Create component tests
   </components>

<content>
   For content in the application:
   - Structure content in markdown or MDX
   - Use frontmatter for metadata
   - Implement content collections
   - Follow consistent naming conventions
   - Optimize images and media
   - Consider internationalization
   </content>

<styling>
   For CSS and styling:
   - Use Tailwind utilities consistently
   - Follow responsive design principles
   - Maintain a consistent design system
   - Create reusable utility classes
   - Consider dark mode support
   - Ensure cross-browser compatibility
   - Optimize CSS for performance
   </styling>


<testing>
   For testing:
   - Write unit tests for business logic
   - Create component tests
   - Implement end-to-end tests for critical flows
   - Use mocks and stubs appropriately
   - Follow testing pyramid principles
   - Test for accessibility
   - Maintain test coverage reports
   </testing>

   

   <deployment>
   For deployment:
   - Optimize build output
   - Configure proper caching strategies
   - Set up CI/CD pipelines
   - Implement proper error monitoring
   - Configure analytics
   - Follow staging -> production workflow
   - Document deployment procedures
   </deployment>
